    "answer": "A",
    "explanation": "Indifference curves show all combinations of two goods that give the consumer equal total utility. They are downward-sloping and convex to the origin due to the diminishing marginal rate of substitution (MRS). The budget line shows all affordable combinations given income and prices; its slope is the price ratio (-Px/Py). A change in the price of one good rotates the budget line, while a change in income shifts it parallel. Consumer equilibrium occurs where the budget line is tangent to the highest attainable indifference curve, meaning MRS equals the price ratio. For an inferior good, the income effect of a price fall is negative (consumers buy less as real income rises), which partially offsets the substitution effect. Therefore, A is the correct answer: \"A\"."
