    "explanation": "In the short run, at least one factor of production is fixed. Average fixed cost (AFC) falls continuously as output rises because total fixed cost is spread over more units. Average variable cost (AVC) and marginal cost (MC) are U-shaped due to diminishing marginal returns. The MC curve always intersects both AVC and ATC at their minimum points — when MC is below the average, the average falls; when MC is above, the average rises. A firm should shut down in the short run if price < AVC. In the long run, all costs are variable and the firm exits if price < ATC. Profit maximisation occurs at MC = MR; revenue maximisation at MR = 0. Therefore, C is the correct answer: \"5-6 units\"."
