    "explanation": "This question is testing consumer equilibrium. An indifference curve shows combinations that give the same satisfaction, while the budget line shows the combinations the consumer can afford. Equilibrium is where the highest attainable indifference curve is tangent to the budget line, so MRS equals the price ratio. Therefore, D is correct: \"the maximum combinations of two products that a consumer can buy with a given level of income\" because that tangency condition is the point where the consumer gets the most satisfaction from the available income."
