    "explanation": "The question \"To reduce road congestion caused by parked cars, a local government introduced a system of tradable parking permits. Households were given a permit allowing them to park one car at the adside. Househo\" is about correcting a market failure. The core issue is that private decision-makers ignore costs or benefits imposed on third parties, so private cost or benefit differs from social cost or benefit. A good policy response changes incentives so that the private outcome moves closer to the social optimum. Therefore, D is correct: \"Too many households own cars so the market in permits is very small.\" because it is the policy that best internalises the external effect described in the question."
