    "explanation": "Transfer earnings are the minimum payment a factor must receive to remain in its current use. Economic rent is any payment above transfer earnings. If a teacher earns $30,000 but would stay for $25,000, transfer earnings are $25,000 and economic rent is $5,000. Non-monetary benefits reduce the wage needed to retain workers. Therefore, B is the correct answer."
