    "explanation": "Income redistribution transfers resources from higher to lower-income groups via progressive taxation and transfers. The case rests on diminishing marginal utility of income — an extra dollar provides more welfare to a poor person. However, redistribution creates an equity-efficiency trade-off: higher taxes may reduce work incentives and investment. A progressive income tax takes a higher percentage from higher incomes, reducing post-tax inequality. Redistribution is most appropriate when society values equality more highly than efficiency. Therefore, C is the correct answer: \"Norway is more likely to have a progressive tax system and public sector pensions than India. Norway is likely to have a higher percentage of tax generated from indirect taxes and privately funded pen\"."
