    "answer": "D",
    "explanation": "Market failure occurs when the free market fails to allocate resources efficiently, resulting in a net welfare loss (deadweight loss) to society. Main causes: externalities (costs or benefits affecting third parties), public goods (non-excludable and non-rival, leading to the free-rider problem), information failure, and market power. Allocative efficiency (P=MC) means resources produce exactly what consumers want; productive efficiency means producing at minimum average cost. Pareto efficiency is achieved when no one can be made better off without making someone else worse off. Therefore, D is the correct answer: \"The fall in the total social cost is greater than the fall in the total social benefit.\"."
