    "explanation": "Oligopoly: few interdependent firms. Kinked demand curve explains price rigidity — rivals match price cuts but not increases. Game theory (prisoner's dilemma) shows why collusion is difficult: each firm has an incentive to cheat. Cartels succeed with few firms, high barriers, homogeneous product, and detection/punishment of cheating. Low barriers to entry make cartels unstable because new entrants can undercut the cartel price. Therefore, C is the correct answer: \"ignoring a price rise and copying a price fall De ignoring both a price rise and a price fall\"."
